      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's not uncommon for the wound to look a bit inflamed and ooze a bit of yellow discharge after a cyst removal, especially if it's a minor infection. However, if the redness and warmth persist, or if the discharge is thick, green, or foul-smelling, it's best to get it checked out by your doctor. In the meantime, you can try applying a warm compress to the area and taking an over-the-counter pain reliever to help manage any discomfort.",
